<subSubSection id="C32D654F8E762C4346E1343ECEA9F80E" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8836C48E762C4346E1343ECEA9F80E" blockId="2.[151,1437,1807,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis id="B943EAD68E762C4346E1343ECB3DF846" bold="true" box="[199,335,1915,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Comments.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B358E762C4347D23439C8D6F846" author="Thomas, D. B." box="[500,676,1916,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" refId="ref7485" refString="Thomas, D. B. (1992) Taxonomic synopsis of the asopine Pentatomidae (Heteroptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Thomas Say Foundation Monographs. Volume XVI. Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, iv + 156 pp." type="book" year="1992">Thomas (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D478E762C4344973438C93EF846" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[689,844,1917,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Podisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrispinus">
<emphasis id="B943EAD68E762C4344973438C93EF846" box="[689,844,1917,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">P. nigrispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the dark bifid humeral angles contrasting with the pale and rugulose anterolateral margins of pronotum This species is widespread (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B358E762C43433634E5CAA2F80E" author="Grazia, J. &amp; Del Vecchio, M. C. &amp; Hildebrand, R." pageId="2" pageNumber="573" pagination="302 - 313" refId="ref5217" refString="Grazia, J., Del Vecchio, M. C. &amp; Hildebrand, R. (1985) Estudo das ninfas de heteropteros predadores: I- Podisus connexivus Bergroth, 1891 (Pentatomidae, Asopinae). Anais da Sociedade Entomologica do Brasil, 14, 302 - 313." type="journal article" year="1985">
Grazia 
<emphasis id="B943EAD68E762C43434234E4CFE7F86A" box="[1380,1429,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">et al</emphasis>
. 1985
</bibRefCitation>
) and show potential in controlling populations of phytophagous insects (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B358E762C4342263481CEBDF80E" author="Grazia, J. &amp; Panizzi, A. R. &amp; Greve, C. &amp; Schwertner, C. F. &amp; Campos, L. A. &amp; Garbelotto, T. D. A. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[1024,1231,1987,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" pagination="681 - 756" refId="ref5385" refString="Grazia, J., Panizzi, A. R., Greve, C., Schwertner, C. F., Campos, L. A., Garbelotto, T. D. A. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2015) Stink Bugs (Pentatomidae). In: Panizzi, A. R. &amp; Grazia, J. (Eds.), True bugs (Heteroptera) of the Neotropics. Springer, Dordrecht, pp. 681 - 756." type="book chapter" year="2015">
Grazia 
<emphasis id="B943EAD68E762C4342753480CEF6F80E" box="[1107,1156,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
